      "id": "8ba7df4b911d",
      "name": "OrbStack Usage Reminder",
      "prompt": "Check if OrbStack or Docker is actively being used on this Mac. \n\nSteps:\n1. Check if OrbStack app exists: ls /Applications/OrbStack.app\n2. Check for running OrbStack processes: pgrep -fl \"orbstack\\|linuxkit\"\n3. Check Docker status: docker ps 2>/dev/null\n4. Check if OrbStack data folder exists and has content: du -sh /Users/ktoclaw/Library/Group\\ Containers/HUAQ24HBR6.dev.orbstack 2>/dev/null\n\nIf OrbStack data folder exists and is still ~6.9GB (not deleted) and no processes running:\n- Send reminder: \"Hey Master KT, it's been 1 month since we checked OrbStack. It's still sitting at ~6.9GB with no active use. Want me to delete it to free up space?\"\n- Include current disk space: df -h / | tail -1\n\nIf OrbStack has already been deleted or is in active use:\n- Stay silent (no message sent)",
